                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d56">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Monroe</persName>, Secretary of
                        State, to Mr. <persName type="to">McCulloch</persName>, collector.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>
                    </placeName>,<lb/>
                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1817-01-03">
                        <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 3, 1817</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <seg type="margin">[50]</seg> *<hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: There being some
                    reason to believe that the schooner Man gore, which arrived and reported
                    herself, on the 28th of last month, at your port as a South American cruiser,
                    was originally fitted out for her cruise at Baltimore, in violation of our laws,
                    you are particularly requested to put the attorney of the United States in
                    possession of all the testimony which you may have or be able to obtain relative
                    to such a charge. It is not doubted that you will cause every step to be taken
                    calculated to bring to light the real transaction in this case, so that whatever
                    breach of the laws of the United States has taken place may be forthwith
                    punished.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAMES MONROE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
